    "body": "Can confirm: on the server side, we don't abort until we've exceeded the threshold: https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/master/eth/protocols/snap/handler.go#L195. \r\n\r\nI guess the question is why we demand the server to act that way.\r\n\r\nI think there's a reason for that, but I'm not 100% sure why at the moment. We might have to either modify our implementation to be more according to spec, or update the spec (plus add the reasoning behind it) -- cc @karalabe .",
